textAnnotations.description:
WERCE
PEST
PERE
or
Recognizing the beauty of life and its tragie
brevity when taken from us violently, the men
and women of the Oklahoma Department of
Transportation wish to acknowledge the lives
lost in the bombing of the Alfred P. Murrah
Building in Oklahoma City and those killed
in the terrorist attack at the World Trade
Center Twin Towers in New York City by the
presentation of this memotial plaque. We
stand with you in the sure knowledge that
all evil shall be overcome.
Presented this 11th day of September, 2002.
